      <element xsi:type="archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel" name="01.01 AI Capability Map (12 Knowledge Areas)" id="id-8217ee65ddc34d7ea3fa3cf0fc0ddc7c">
        <documentation>Source: AI-BOK v1.0, Module 1, sectie 1-12, p.7</documentation>
        <property key="dct:source" value="AI-BOK v1.0, Module 1, sectie 1-12, p.7"/>
        <child xsi:type="archimate:Note" id="id-0a5cf3ce11bb4e19aff5d230d87636bd">
          <content>Author: Jan Willem van Veen
Modified: 2026-04-02
Source: AI-BOK v1.0, Module 1, sectie 1-12, p.7

The 12 knowledge areas as capabilities, grouped in three layers: Strategy &amp; Direction, Realisation &amp; Operations, Assurance &amp; Accountability. Per KA the associated business function, primary role and goal.</content>
          <bounds x="0" y="0" width="380" height="180"/>
        </child>
